column3: I prefer to plan my tasks well in advance rather than dealing with them spontaneously.
column4: I enjoy engaging in lively discussions and debates with colleagues and students.
column5: I find satisfaction in guiding and mentoring students towards their academic and professional goals.
column6: I tend to keep a professional distance from my students, maintaining a strictly academic relationship.
column7: I enjoy exploring innovative teaching techniques and I see mistakes and setbacks as opportunities for growth and learning rather than reasons for discouragement.
column8: I prioritize academic excellence above all else, even if it means pushing students to their limits.
column9: I am passionate about my subject area and enjoy sharing my enthusiasm with others.
column10: I am patient and understanding when working with students who are struggling academically.
column11: I believe in the importance of ethics and integrity in academic research and teaching.
column12: I value creativity and encourage my students to think outside the box in their assignments and projects
